<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">An inner-city precinct driven by lifestyle, walkability and a concentration of cultural amenity.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      South Brisbane sits directly across the river from the CBD, less than one kilometre from the Brisbane city centre by foot. It is one of the few suburbs in Brisbane where a resident can walk to work, walk to a world-class art gallery, walk to a riverfront parkland and be back in time for dinner on Grey Street, all without getting in a car. That combination is not available anywhere else in the city at this proximity to the CBD, and it is the fundamental reason South Brisbane continues to attract lifestyle-driven buyers who are willing to pay for the precinct.
    </p>
