    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about South Brisbane.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in South Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">South Brisbane property values are driven by proximity to the CBD, the amenity of South Bank Parklands, and the concentration of cultural institutions along Grey Street and Melbourne Street. Boutique apartment buildings with river views or direct access to the parklands consistently attract the strongest buyer interest. The suburb's position less than one kilometre from the Brisbane CBD means genuine walkability to major employment is a structural feature of every property in the precinct.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a property in South Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented South Brisbane apartments in quality boutique buildings typically sell within 30 to 50 days. The buyer pool is drawn from CBD professionals, downsizers and investors who understand the rental demand generated by the South Bank precinct. Campaign strategy needs to clearly differentiate boutique quality from the broader apartment market to achieve the best result.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in South Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">South Brisbane offers one of Brisbane's most complete inner-city lifestyles. South Bank Parklands provides 17 hectares of riverfront parkland, beach, restaurants and event space immediately accessible on foot. GOMA, QPAC, the State Library of Queensland and the Brisbane Convention and Exhibition Centre are all within walking distance. Grey Street and Melbourne Street provide a dense strip of dining and retail, and the CBD is walkable across the river via the Goodwill or Victoria bridges.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is South Brisbane a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">South Brisbane's structural appeal is its concentration of amenity relative to its distance from the CBD. Buyers who prioritise walkability, cultural precinct access and inner-city lifestyle over land content consistently find that South Brisbane delivers a quality of daily life that is difficult to replicate elsewhere in Brisbane. The constraint on quality supply in boutique buildings means well-presented properties in the precinct continue to attract competitive interest from a motivated buyer pool.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

